<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1206">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7052.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Confidential Agent of the
                                    Constitutionalist Government</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I refer to our recent
                            conversation on the matter of Los Mochis and I am pleased to inform your
                            excellency that in a telegram dated at Monterey December 1, Mr. Carranza
                            advises me that the recent successes of our troops on the revolutionists
                            have brought as a result that Los Mochis be occupied by our forces.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Carranza further states that our Government will afford every
                            guaranty and protection on lives and property at that place to both <pb facs="0972" n="856" xml:id="pg_856"/> nationals and foreigners in
                            the same way as it has been done heretofore in every place controlled by
                            our Government.</p>
                        <p>I renew [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Arredondo.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>